{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-jsx","path":"/post-five","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>In your home folder you should have the following directory:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\">~$ .ipython/profile_default/startup/</code></pre></div>\n<p>If you make a <code class=\"language-text\">.py</code> file there it will be run every time that <code class=\"language-text\">ipython</code> is started. </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> os\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> ipdb\nos<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>environ<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">'PYTHONBREAKPOINT'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">'ipdb.set_trace'</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>This will allow you to use <code class=\"language-text\">breakpoint()</code> in your scripts and it will trigger the <code class=\"language-text\">ipdb</code> debugger.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\"><span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token operator\">/</span>home<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>rick<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>dev<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>chemcurator_django<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>chemreg<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>compound<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>validators<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>py<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">110</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>validate_smiles<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token number\">109</span>         breakpoint<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token number\">110</span>         ps<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>ParseSmiles<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>smiles<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> partial<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token boolean\">False</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token number\">111</span>     <span class=\"token keyword\">except</span> ps<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>ValenceError<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n\nipdb<span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token builtin\">type</span> your commands here!</code></pre></div>\n<p>The details can be found in the <a href=\"https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0553/\">docs</a></p>","frontmatter":{"date":"2020-04-15","title":"Using ipdb with breakpoint in python","subtitle":"National Aquatic Resource Survey method of snapping pour points","tags":["tutorial","javascript","frontend"],"cover":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7777777777777777,"src":"/static/a19bb49c74e08d73b9a4290560dcb1c4/a69c3/the_horse.jpg","srcSet":"/static/a19bb49c74e08d73b9a4290560dcb1c4/6b948/the_horse.jpg 480w,\n/static/a19bb49c74e08d73b9a4290560dcb1c4/d1e22/the_horse.jpg 960w,\n/static/a19bb49c74e08d73b9a4290560dcb1c4/a69c3/the_horse.jpg 1440w","srcWebp":"/static/a19bb49c74e08d73b9a4290560dcb1c4/933da/the_horse.webp","srcSetWebp":"/static/a19bb49c74e08d73b9a4290560dcb1c4/83f4f/the_horse.webp 480w,\n/static/a19bb49c74e08d73b9a4290560dcb1c4/ce114/the_horse.webp 960w,\n/static/a19bb49c74e08d73b9a4290560dcb1c4/933da/the_horse.webp 1440w","sizes":"(max-width: 1440px) 100vw, 1440px"},"resize":{"src":"/static/a19bb49c74e08d73b9a4290560dcb1c4/a6c62/the_hors